<br>
There is only one person who can tell you if the shooting was justified and that is the officer invovled. It doesnt matter if you have witnesses who say it wasnt, it all depends on the perception of the officer at the time of the incident. Remember this was obviously a long vehicle pursuit. In pursuits you become tunnel visoned. Adrenaline  levels going up and down putting some serious fatigue on your body. A 10 minute pursuit is enough to cause serious mental fatigue as well as physical. You are trying to think about many variables at the same time, Officer safety, Public safety, where to roadblock, notifying other jurisdictions, etc.<br>
<br>
This pursuit could of ended very easily but by the choices of the suspect but he continued to flee. Remember the decision this officer made was split second. He doesnt have the luxury of taking days, weeks to come to his decsion like the investigators or newspapers do. The question that is going to be asked during this investigation is a simple one. Would a reasonable officer with similar training and experience shoot the suspect. Once that question is anwsered the investigation is pretty much over and either deemed justified or not. I wasnt there and cant tell you if it was justified or not but I definately feel sorry for the officer who will remember this day forever and always wonder if he could of done something different.<br>
