  This is Maeghant on Air's computer.  The cop statements have already been said, so I got nothing much to add, except I don't think anyone has mentioned that (correct me if I'm wrong) a car is considered a &quot;deadly weapon&quot; in those circumstances.  As in, if you attempt to run someone over, it's attempted murder, just as if you attempt to shoot a gun at someone.<br>
<br>
  Doesn't matter if you are simply trying to shoot at a cop to scare him or try to run around a cop to avoid him.  In that case, the suspect was using deadly force and the cop is allowed to respond.  Cars are taken very seriously.<br>
<br>
  Now, how acceptable that policy is might be subject to discussion.  I don't know how often a car is actually used as a weapon and causes injury as opposed to the number of fatalities caused by firearms, etc etc blah.<br>
<br>
